{"data":[{"type":"questionAttempts","id":"17633588","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionAttempts/17633588"},"attributes":{"position":0,"marks":1,"score":0,"answeredAt":"2025-09-30T17:55:15+09:30","options":[1],"response":null,"finalizedAt":"2025-09-30T17:55:15+09:30"},"relationships":{"user":{"data":{"type":"users","id":"50098"}},"questionSession":{"data":null},"session":{"data":null},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"17487"}},"bookmark":{"data":null}}}],"included":[{"type":"questions","id":"17487","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questions/17487"},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"10177"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"70937"}}}},{"type":"items","id":"10177","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/items/10177"},"attributes":{"contentType":"question"},"relationships":{"content":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"17487"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"56404"}},"tags":{"data":[{"type":"tags","id":"67"},{"type":"tags","id":"71"},{"type":"tags","id":"76"},{"type":"tags","id":"4948"},{"type":"tags","id":"5389"}]},"contributions":{"data":[{"type":"contributions","id":"23785"},{"type":"contributions","id":"23880"}]}},"meta":{"canRevise":false,"canManage":false,"canDelete":false}},{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"70937","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionRevisions/70937"},"attributes":{"stem":"\u003Cp\u003EA researcher is evaluating a new diagnostic test for coeliac disease. In a study of 1000 patients, the following results were obtained:\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cul\u003E\u003Cli\u003E200 patients had coeliac disease confirmed by reference standard\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E800 patients did not have coeliac disease\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003EThe new test correctly identified 750 patients without coeliac disease\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003EThe new test correctly identified 160 patients with coeliac disease\u003C/li\u003E\u003C/ul\u003E","stemQuestion":"Which one of the following best describes the specificity of this diagnostic test?","responseType":"sba","marks":1,"options":["0.90","0.75","0.93","0.65","0.85"],"correctOptions":[2],"correctResponses":null,"explanation":"\u003Cp\u003EThe specificity of a diagnostic test is the proportion of true negatives correctly identified among all patients who do not have the condition. It is calculated as:\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003ESpecificity = True Negatives \u00f7 (True Negatives + False Positives)\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EIn this case:\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cul\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cp\u003ETrue Negatives = 750 (correctly identified as not having coeliac disease)\u003C/p\u003E\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cp\u003ETotal without disease = 800\u003C/p\u003E\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cp\u003ETherefore, False Positives = 50 (800 - 750)\u003C/p\u003E\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cp\u003ESpecificity = 750 \u00f7 (750 + 50) = 750 \u00f7 800 = \u003Cstrong\u003E0.93\u003C/strong\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\u003C/li\u003E\u003C/ul\u003E\u003Cp\u003EA test with high specificity is particularly useful for ruling in a diagnosis when positive, as it has few false positives.\u003C/p\u003E","optionExplanations":["","","","",""],"learningPoints":["Specificity measures the proportion of true negatives correctly identified by a diagnostic test.","Specificity is calculated as true negatives divided by the sum of true negatives and false positives.","A highly specific test is most useful for ruling in a condition when positive."],"references":["Sullivan LM. Essentials of biostatistics in public health. 3rd ed. Burlington (MA): Jones \u0026 Bartlett Learning; 2018.","Dawson B, Trapp RG. Basic \u0026 clinical biostatistics. 4th ed. New York: McGraw-Hill; 2004."]},"relationships":{"itemRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"56404"}},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"17487"}},"stemMedia":{"data":[]},"explanationMedia":{"data":[]}}},{"type":"itemRevisions","id"